      "content": "so you're saying one side is a \"moral imperative\" and the other is just a \"secondary\" concern about implementation? that's a pretty huge distinction to make. if a policy is economically disastrous or causes massive shortages, does the \"moral imperative\" even matter? aren't those two things equally important to the actual outcome for a country?",
